// 1. Selecting entire line by clicking number before it.
// 2. CTRL + / : To comment out selected text.
// 3. CTRL + X : Cut the line.
// 4. CTRL + D : To select each occurences of a word one at a time. 
// 5. CTRL + SHIFT + L : To select all occurence of that word.
// 6. CTRL + Z : Undo.
// 7. SHIFT + ALT + Cursor : To select column of text.
// 8. ALT + Cursor : To multiselect.
// 9. CTRL + C : To copy entire line without selecting.
// 10. CTRL + V : To paste entire line.
// 11. ALT + Arrow : To move entire line up and down.
// 12. ALT + SHIFT : To duplicate line up and down.
// 13. CTRL + SPACE : To show suggestions.
// 14. CTRL + P : To display the search bar.
// 15. CTRL + B : To toggle the sidebar.
// 16. CTRL + O : To open the current file
// 17. f2 : To rename files.
// 18. f7 : To run code.
// 19. END : To kill all terminal.
// 20. DELETE : To delete terminal.
// 21. SHIFT + DELETE : To delete files.